<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="deal-vi">deal <strong><em>vi</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /diːl/    美 /diːl/  </p>
<p>(dealt, dealt)</p>
<h2 id="_1">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="deal-in">deal in</h3>
<p>1.<strong>经营；买卖：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The company deals in computer software.
这个公司经营计算机软件。</p></div>

<h3 id="deal-with">deal with</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>处理；对付；应付 (handle)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I can’t control what happens to me, but I can choose how I deal with it. 
我无法掌控发生在自己身上的事，但我能选择如何应对。</p><footer>2016 北京</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She’s used to dealing with all kinds of people in her job.
她习惯于在工作中同各种各样的人打交道。</p></div>

<p>2.★ <strong>涉及；论及：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>This book deals with the ancient history of China.
这本书讲述了中国的古代史。</p></div>

<p>3.★ <strong>和...做生意</strong><br />
to do business with sb：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In many people’s opinion, that company, though relatively small, is pleasant to deal with.  
许多人认为那家公司虽小，但跟它做生意却很愉快。</p><footer>2010 四川</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>dealer /'diːlə(r)/ n [C]   </p></div>